block-worldcom-sprint-merger/|title=DOJ files to block WorldCom-Sprint merger|access-date=2017-02-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170219031128/https://www.cnet.com/uk/news/doj-files-to-block-worldcom-sprint-merger/|archive-date=2017-02-19|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>https://www.cnet.com/news/mci-worldcom-buys-sprint-for-129-billion/</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 6\n| 2014\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Pfizer]]\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Astra Zeneca]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|123.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|123|2014}}\n|Significant concerns were raised by the [[UK Government]] over job security, in the end leading to a deal being abandoned due to resistance from the AstraZeneca Board.<ref name=\"wolfstreet.com\"/>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 7\n| 2018\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Broadcom Ltd]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Qualcomm Inc]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|121.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|121|2018}}\n| Qualcomm claimed that Broadcom had undervalued the business but did propose to meet Broadcom officials, with the initial offer of $121 billion ($140 billion with debt).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-43401675|title=Trump pressure scuppers $140bn tech deal|date=14 March 2018|via=www.bbc.co.uk|access-date=14 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181014164924/https://www.bbc.com/news/business-43401675|archive-date=14 October 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/us-qualcomm-m-a-broadcom/qualcomm-rejects-broadcoms-revised-buyout-offer-proposes-meeting-idUKKBN1FS391|title=Qualcomm warns of customer losses, legal hazards to Broadcom buyout|first=Sonam|last=Rai|access-date=2018-02-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180210001643/https://uk.reuters.com/article/us-qualcomm-m-a-broadcom/qualcomm-rejects-broadcoms-revised-buyout-offer-proposes-meeting-idUKKBN1FS391|archive-date=2018-02-10|url-status=live}}<