eca]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|106.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|106|2014}}\n| AstraZeneca claimed the deal undervalued the company.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2014/may/19/astrazeneca-board-reject-pfizer-takeover-bid|title=AstraZeneca rejects Pfizer's final \u00a369bn takeover bid|first1=Sean|last1=Farrell|first2=Rowena|last2=Mason|date=19 May 2014|via=The Guardian|access-date=18 February 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170219004659/https://www.theguardian.com/business/2014/may/19/astrazeneca-board-reject-pfizer-takeover-bid|archive-date=19 February 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>https://www.reuters.com/article/us-astrazeneca-pfizer-idUSBREA3R0H520140502</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 11\n| 2018\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Broadcom Ltd]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Qualcomm Inc]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|103.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|103|2018}}\n|$130 billion with assumed debt ($103 billion without), Qualcomm shareholders would get $60 in cash and $10 per share in Broadcom shares. Qualcomm rejected Broadcom's $103 billion takeover bid, saying the offer \u201cdramatically\u201d undervalued the U.S. company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/us-qualcomm-m-a-broadcom/qualcomm-rejects-broadcoms-103-billion-takeover-proposal-idUKKBN1DD1NU|title=Qualcomm rejects Broadcom's $103-billion takeover bid|first=Supantha Mukherjee and Munsif|last=Vengattil|website=reuters.com|accessdate=22 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171121152535/https://uk.reuters.com/article/us-qualcomm-m-a-broadcom/qualcomm-rejects-broadcoms-103-billion-takeover-proposal-idUKKBN1DD1NU|archive-date=21 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-qualcomm-m-a-broadcom/broadcom-offers-103-billion-for-qualcomm-sets-up-takeover-battle-idUKKBN1D61EK|title=Broadcom bids $103 billion for Qualcomm, open to going hostile|first=Supantha Mukherjee and Greg|last=Roumeliotis|website=reuters.com|accessdate=22 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171118003948/https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-qualcomm-m-a-broadcom/broadcom-offers-103-billion-for-qualcomm-sets-up-takeover-battle-idUKKBN1D61EK|archive-date=18 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 12\n| 2014\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Pfizer]]\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Astra Zeneca]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|98.9\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|98.9|2014}}\n| AstraZeneca claimed the deal undervalued the company.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-astrazeneca-pfizer-idUSBREA3R0H520140428|title=Pfizer chases AstraZeneca for potential $100 billion deal|date=28 April 2017|via=Reuters|access-date=2 July 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170219013934/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-astrazeneca-pfizer-idUSBREA3R0H520140428|archive-date=19 February 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 13\n| 2016\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Honeywell]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[United Technologies]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|90.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|90|2016}}\n| Honeywell dropped a bid to acquire United Technologies, citing potential regulatory hurdles.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/honeywell-ends-pursuit-of-united-technologies-1456841533|title=Honeywell Ends Chase for United Technologies|first=Ted|last=Mann|date=2 March 2016|via=www.wsj.com|access-date=4 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170831203614/https://www.wsj.com/articles/honeywell-ends-pursuit-of-united-technologies-1456841533|archive-date=31 August 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.utc.com/News/News-Center/Pages/United-Technologies-Comments-On-Recent-News-Reports.aspx|title=United Technologies Comments On Recent News Reports|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170219142927/http://ww