 billion or larger) from 2020 to 2029:\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n!Rank\n!Year\n!Purchaser\n!Purchased\n!Transaction value<br/><small>(in billions USD) {{font color|red|(with debt)}}</small>\n!Inflation adjusted<br/><small>(in billions USD) {{font color|red|(with debt)}}</small>\n!Ref\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| 2020\n| {{flagicon|UK}} [[Aon plc]]\n| {{flagicon|UK}} [[Willis Towers Watson]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|30.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|30|2020}}\n|<ref>https://www.wsj.com/articles/aon-to-merge-with-willis-towers-watson-in-all-stock-deal-valued-at-30-billion-11583758247</ref><ref group=\"N\">Not Completed</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==State owned enterprises==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n!Rank\n!Year\n!Purchaser\n!Purchased\n!Total asset value<br/>{{nowrap|<small>(billions USD)</small>}}\n!Inflation adjusted<br/>{{nowrap|<small>(billions USD)</small>}}\n!Note\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1\n| 2017\n| {{flagicon|CHN}} [[Shenhua Group]]\n| {{flagicon|CHN}} [[China Guodian Corporation]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|278.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|278|2017}}\n| In August 2017, [[State-owned Assets Supervision and Administration Commission of the State Council|SASAC]] announced that [[China Guodian Corporation]] (one of China's largest coal-fired power generators) and [[Shenhua Group]] (China\u2019s biggest coal miner) would be jointly restructured, with Shenhua Group becoming [[China Energy Investment Corporation]] and absorbing China Guodian Corporation to become the largest power company in the world by installed capacity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/us-china-power-shenhua-guodian-analysis-idUKKCN1B918C|title=Power of love: China's latest arranged match rattles utilities|first=Meng Meng and Josephine|last=Mason|website=reuters.com|accessdate=22 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170907175837