ates Department of Justice Antitrust Division|Antitrust Division]] of the [[United States Department of Justice]] formally announced that it would seek to block the takeover, and filed a lawsuit to such effect in federal court.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2011-08-31/u-s-files-antitrust-complaint-to-block-proposed-at-t-t-mobile-merger|title=T-Mobile Antitrust Challenge Gives AT&T Little Recourse|via=www.bloomberg.com|access-date=2017-03-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170910020052/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2011-08-31/u-s-files-antitrust-complaint-to-block-proposed-at-t-t-mobile-merger|archive-date=2017-09-10|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 44\n| 2019\n| {{flagicon|HKG}} [[Hong Kong Stock Exchange]] \n| {{flagicon|GBR}} [[London Stock Exchange]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 39.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|39|2019}}\n| $39 billion takeover proposal was rejected by the Board of the London Stock Exchange.<ref>https://uk.reuters.com/article/us-lse-m-a-hkexlse/hong-kong-exchange-vows-to-press-on-with-39-billion-lse-bid-after-rebuff-idUKKCN1VY19O</ref><ref>https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-lse-m-a-hong-kong-exchanges/hong-kong-exchange-in-39-billion-bid-for-lse-rivalling-refinitiv-deal-idUKKCN1VW0ZH</ref><ref>https://uk.reuters.com/article/us-lse-m-a-hong-kong-exchanges-refinitiv/lse-confirms-hong-kong-exchanges-proposal-says-committed-to-refinitiv-deal-idUKKCN1VW13U</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 45\n| 1999\n| {{flagicon|BER}}{{flagicon|USA}} [[Global Crossing]] \n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[US West]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 37.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|37|1999}}\n| Global Crossing lost out on acquiring US West after [[Qwest]] outbid them.<ref>https://money.cnn.com/1999/05/17/deals/crossing/</ref><ref>https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB932332524549345218</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 46\n| 2015 \n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[A