71031222401/https://uk.reuters.com/article/us-rockwell-automat-m-a-emerson-electric/rockwell-automation-rejects-emersons-27-billion-offer-idUKKBN1D01SM|archive-date=31 October 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/brief-rockwell-automation-says-board-rej/brief-rockwell-automation-says-board-rejected-takeover-proposals-from-emerson-idUKASB0BPY0|title=BRIEF-Rockwell Automation says board rejected takeover proposals from Emerson|first=Reuters|last=Editorial|website=reuters.com|accessdate=22 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171115221825/https://uk.reuters.com/article/brief-rockwell-automation-says-board-rej/brief-rockwell-automation-says-board-rejected-takeover-proposals-from-emerson-idUKASB0BPY0|archive-date=15 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 69\n| 2001\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} [[Prudential plc]] \n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[American General]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 26.5 \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{inflation|US|26.5|2001}} \n| Prudential\u2019s bid of $26.5 billion in stock was reduced to just over $20 billion when Prudential\u2019s shares plummeted after the announcement. [[AIG]] then stepped in and offered $23 billion which was accepted by American General.<ref>http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/business/1324691.stm</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 70\n| 2017\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[PPG Industries]]\n| {{flagicon|NED}} [[Akzo Nobel]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|26.1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|26.1|2017}}\n| Akzo rejected the unsolicited offer, claiming the revised offer was still too low, Akzo claimed that key stakeholder issues as well as uncertainties and risks that had already been raised in response to earlier offers had not been answered proposal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/us-akzo-nobel-m-a-ppg-idUKKBN1751J6|title=Akzo Nobel CEO says PPG proposal is insufficient|first=Reuters|last=Editorial|website=reuters.com|accessdate=22 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170523132001/http://uk.reuters.com/article/us-akzo-nobel-m-a-ppg-idUKKBN1751J6|archive-date=23 May 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 71\n| 2007\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Express Scripts]] \n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Caremark Rx]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 26.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{inflation|US|26|2007}} \n| Express Scripts bid $26 billion for Caremark Rx but refused to pay a $675 million breakup fee to void Caremark's pending merger with [[CVS Health|CVS]]. Even though Express Scripts offered $4 billion more than CVS, CVS and Caremark Rx completed their merger.<ref>https://www.reuters.com/article/caremark-lawsuit-idUSN1030407320070110</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 72\n| 2015 \n| {{flagicon|NED}}{{flagicon|USA}} [[Mylan]] \n| {{flagicon|IRL}}{{flagicon|USA}} [[Perrigo]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 26.0\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{inflation|US|26|2015}} \n| In order for the hostile takeover to go through successfully, Mylan needed 50% of Perrigos shares to be tendered under the deal. However, only 40% or 58 million shares were tendered and the hostile takeover fell through.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fortune.com/2015/11/13/mylan-perrigo-hostile/|title=Mylan's Hostile Bid for Perrigo Fails|access-date=2017-03-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211235522/http://fortune.com/2015/11/13/mylan-perrigo-hostile/|archive-date=2017-02-11|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 73\n| 2002\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Hughes Electronics Corp.]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[EchoStar]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|25.6\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{inflation|US|25.6|2002}}\n| US and state anti-trust enforcers filed a lawsuit to halt the deal, claiming that the deal would eliminate competition and adversely effect consumers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestreet.com/story/12714173/2/5-government-blocked-mergers-